00:05:39.300 --> 00:05:40.870
we couldn't even
afford a hard drive

00:05:40.870 --> 00:05:43.080
that we could put 24
hours of video onto.

00:05:43.080 --> 00:05:45.790
It was actually
quite costly. $1,000.

00:05:45.790 --> 00:05:47.482
But I followed Moore's law.

00:05:47.482 --> 00:05:49.940
And figured that by the time
I finished all of these videos

00:05:49.940 --> 00:05:52.250
around the world, I
would be able to afford

00:05:52.250 --> 00:05:55.070
the adequate hard
drives to do this.

00:05:55.070 --> 00:05:57.050
So let's see.

00:05:57.050 --> 00:06:00.050
So one of the big questions
that Global Lives is asking--

00:06:00.050 --> 00:06:02.680
and Global Lives really
is not about giving you

00:06:02.680 --> 00:06:03.580
specific answers.

00:06:03.580 --> 00:06:05.660
It's about asking you questions.

00:06:05.660 --> 00:06:09.500
One of these questions is
what are the boundaries

00:06:09.500 --> 00:06:12.460
of your moral universe?

00:06:12.460 --> 00:06:14.320
And this is a
pretty big question.

00:06:14.320 --> 00:06:19.370
And one way I like to think
about what this might mean

00:06:19.370 --> 00:06:20.900
is to ask people a question.

00:06:20.900 --> 00:06:25.580
So I'm curious in the audience
here if anyone knows or would

00:06:25.580 --> 00:06:28.370
like to volunteer a number
about how many people

00:06:28.370 --> 00:06:34.530
died in Iraq as a result
of the Iraq war since 2002.

00:06:34.530 --> 00:06:37.010
If anyone has an idea
about the numbers there,

00:06:37.010 --> 00:06:39.250
the magnitude of
deaths that took place.

00:06:39.250 --> 00:06:40.990
AUDIENCE: 300,000.

00:06:40.990 --> 00:06:43.255
DAVID EVAN HARRIS: 300,000.

00:06:43.255 --> 00:06:45.070
600,000.

00:06:45.070 --> 00:06:45.790
Anyone else?

00:06:45.790 --> 00:06:49.070
No Googling allowed.

00:06:49.070 --> 00:06:50.440
1 million?

00:06:50.440 --> 00:06:52.101
Couple million.

00:06:52.101 --> 00:06:52.600
Yeah.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:54.270
So this is really interesting.

00:06:54.270 --> 00:06:56.840
And so this room is
actually representative

00:06:56.840 --> 00:07:00.570
of the broader lack of
agreement on this issue.

00:07:00.570 --> 00:07:03.680
There are estimates
that range from 150,000

00:07:03.680 --> 00:07:05.660
to a million people.

00:07:05.660 --> 00:07:08.015
Just one of the studies
reached a conclusion

00:07:08.015 --> 00:07:09.960
that around half
a million people

00:07:09.960 --> 00:07:11.740
died as a result of this war.

00:07:11.740 --> 00:07:15.420
Now to me, this is
really difficult,

00:07:15.420 --> 00:07:17.580
because we do have
exact numbers.

00:07:17.580 --> 00:07:21.220
And we do get exact
numbers whenever

00:07:21.220 --> 00:07:23.690
members of the American
military or US citizens

00:07:23.690 --> 00:07:25.460
are killed in these conflicts.

00:07:25.460 --> 00:07:30.570
But we have a margin of error
in the hundreds of thousands

00:07:30.570 --> 00:07:34.300
of human lives in our
reporting on this issue.

00:07:34.300 --> 00:07:36.840
And to me, what that
says is that there's

00:07:36.840 --> 00:07:39.530
a really deep problem
in our society today,

00:07:39.530 --> 00:07:42.910
which is that we don't
value human lives equally.

00:07:42.910 --> 00:07:46.510
And if someone is of
a different religion,

00:07:46.510 --> 00:07:51.520
of a different nationality,
and maybe of a different class,

00:07:51.520 --> 00:07:53.630
and living in a different
part of the world,

00:07:53.630 --> 00:07:58.210
we don't have the mechanisms to
really think about their life

00:07:58.210 --> 00:08:00.440
in the same way,
in the way that we

00:08:00.440 --> 00:08:02.140
think about the
lives of other people

00:08:02.140 --> 00:08:03.554
that are much closer to us.

00:08:03.554 --> 00:08:05.220
So to me, that's a
really important part

00:08:05.220 --> 00:08:09.515
of the context of why I started
thinking about Global Lives.

00:08:09.515 --> 00:08:11.140
So I'm going to show
a short video that

00:08:11.140 --> 00:08:13.130
gives you an introduction
to Global Lives.

00:08:13.130 --> 00:08:14.827
And then I'll tell you more.

