00:08:17.510 --> 00:08:21.410
-The world is an
incredibly diverse place.

00:08:21.410 --> 00:08:25.300
But it takes experiencing that
diversity on a personal level

00:08:25.300 --> 00:08:27.330
to really appreciate
and understand it.

00:08:32.049 --> 00:08:34.500
-The Global Lives project
is a video library

00:08:34.500 --> 00:08:36.820
of life experience
where we record

00:08:36.820 --> 00:08:40.950
24 hours in the daily life of
people from all walks of life,

00:08:40.950 --> 00:08:42.180
from all over the world.

00:08:42.180 --> 00:08:43.554
-What I think is
very interesting

00:08:43.554 --> 00:08:45.770
is the way in which
we present it.

00:08:45.770 --> 00:08:49.900
Unraveling in real time,
waking up, eating breakfast,

00:08:49.900 --> 00:08:51.550
conversing with your neighbors.

00:08:51.550 --> 00:08:54.932
-It's those details that really
make you connect with someone.

00:08:54.932 --> 00:08:56.390
All over the world,
no matter where

00:08:56.390 --> 00:08:59.390
we are, how we live, we
all laugh, we all cry,

00:08:59.390 --> 00:09:01.890
we all care about our families.

00:09:01.890 --> 00:09:04.450
-Global Lives
cultivates empathy.

00:09:04.450 --> 00:09:08.010
And empathy is at the foundation
of any thriving culture.

00:09:08.010 --> 00:09:11.170
-It all began with recording the
life of James Bullock, a cable

00:09:11.170 --> 00:09:14.280
car driver here in San
Francisco back in 2004.

00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:16.750
Since then, we've done video
shoots in other countries

00:09:16.750 --> 00:09:20.660
around the world, including
Brazil, Malawi, Japan, China,

00:09:20.660 --> 00:09:25.990
India, Indonesia, Serbia,
Lebanon, and Kazakhstan.

00:09:25.990 --> 00:09:27.420
-When selecting
our participants,

00:09:27.420 --> 00:09:29.180
we work with
demographics experts

00:09:29.180 --> 00:09:32.710
to represent the world's
diversity by age, religion,

00:09:32.710 --> 00:09:36.030
income, gender, and occupation.

00:09:36.030 --> 00:09:39.520
-It's really transformative to
travel and see other cultures.

00:09:39.520 --> 00:09:41.020
But not everyone
has the privilege

00:09:41.020 --> 00:09:43.380
to just backpack
around the world

00:09:43.380 --> 00:09:45.760
and get to know people
from different places.

00:09:45.760 --> 00:09:48.170
Global Lives tries to
bring that to people where

00:09:48.170 --> 00:09:51.560
they are, through the internet,
through video installations,

00:09:51.560 --> 00:09:54.470
and allow people to have
that experience of seeing

00:09:54.470 --> 00:09:57.820
what everyday life is like in
different places in the world.

00:09:57.820 --> 00:09:59.350
-In a classroom
environment, it's

00:09:59.350 --> 00:10:03.600
very important for the
future leaders of this world

00:10:03.600 --> 00:10:06.580
to be able to appreciate
cultures, and be

00:10:06.580 --> 00:10:09.260
able to understand that
at the root of it all,

00:10:09.260 --> 00:10:13.756
we are all human beings with
the same aspirations and dreams.

00:10:13.756 --> 00:10:16.890
-The Global Lives collective is
made up volunteer filmmakers,

00:10:16.890 --> 00:10:20.570
photographers, designers,
architects, and everyday people

00:10:20.570 --> 00:10:23.420
from all over the world who
are dedicated to sharing

00:10:23.420 --> 00:10:26.169
culture and crossing
cultural boundaries.

00:10:26.169 --> 00:10:28.460
-There's so many ways and
opportunities to get involved

00:10:28.460 --> 00:10:29.730
with the Global Lives Project.

00:10:29.730 --> 00:10:33.120
Even just coming to our
website and helping tag videos,

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:35.470
there's plenty of opportunities
to use our resources

00:10:35.470 --> 00:10:38.634
and engage in that,
and contribute to that.

