00:14:08.400 --> 00:14:11.260
DAVID EVAN HARRIS:
So those animations

00:14:11.260 --> 00:14:12.760
came out of this
spreadsheet, again.

00:14:12.760 --> 00:14:15.170
So what we tried to do is
we developed this concept

00:14:15.170 --> 00:14:17.710
of a representativity score.

00:14:17.710 --> 00:14:20.420
And this is actually
something that

00:14:20.420 --> 00:14:22.700
came from an idea in a
conversation I had with Loren

00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:25.310
Carpenter, who's one of
the founders of Pixar,

00:14:25.310 --> 00:14:27.500
and invented the software
called RenderMan.

00:14:27.500 --> 00:14:30.824
And I told him, Loren, we're
about to finish our 10th shoot.

00:14:30.824 --> 00:14:32.740
But we want to keep doing
more of these shoots

00:14:32.740 --> 00:14:33.531
all over the world.

00:14:33.531 --> 00:14:35.120
And we want to
stick to this idea.

00:14:35.120 --> 00:14:36.080
And he said, oh, David.

00:14:36.080 --> 00:14:37.330
It's a simple problem.

00:14:37.330 --> 00:14:39.975
All you need to do is create a
seven dimensional million cell

00:14:39.975 --> 00:14:41.470
by million cell matrix.

00:14:41.470 --> 00:14:43.630
And then in that
matrix, you'll be

00:14:43.630 --> 00:14:46.625
able to maximize the
distance between all

00:14:46.625 --> 00:14:49.000
the different points in each
of the different dimensions.

00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:50.931
And just write an algorithm.

00:14:50.931 --> 00:14:52.180
And then it will all work out.

00:14:52.180 --> 00:14:54.760
And it will guide how you
keep adding to the collection.

00:14:54.760 --> 00:14:57.630
And so we're in the process
of implementing Loren's idea

00:14:57.630 --> 00:14:59.190
through first a set
of spreadsheets,

00:14:59.190 --> 00:15:01.080
and eventually we hope
an online tool that

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:03.490
will allow people to come
to our website and say,

00:15:03.490 --> 00:15:05.830
I'd like to produce a
new Global Lives shoot.

00:15:05.830 --> 00:15:10.500
How can I propose a person who
adds the most representativity

00:15:10.500 --> 00:15:12.670
to the Global Lives collection?

