00:44:05.510 --> 00:44:09.040
And so in an installation
format, when you're

00:44:09.040 --> 00:44:13.270
stepping inside and seeing the
unraveling of a daily life,

00:44:13.270 --> 00:44:16.320
you might come upon a very
mundane moment, you know.

00:44:16.320 --> 00:44:17.970
Someone is just
hiking up a mountain.

00:44:17.970 --> 00:44:20.500
Someone else is
brushing their teeth.

00:44:20.500 --> 00:44:27.100
And so that forces you to
rethink what narrative is,

00:44:27.100 --> 00:44:31.710
and to rethink the fact that
we put a lot of narratives

00:44:31.710 --> 00:44:33.940
on everything we
see in the media.

00:44:33.940 --> 00:44:34.440
Right?

00:44:34.440 --> 00:44:35.939
There's always some
sort of opinion.

00:44:35.939 --> 00:44:40.670
And so this is as pure as
possible in terms of cinema

00:44:40.670 --> 00:44:42.440
verite, just unraveling.

00:44:42.440 --> 00:44:48.890
And that allows us to ask those
questions and begin dialogue.

