00:47:18.740 --> 00:47:20.830
we've developed a couple
of different surveys.

00:47:20.830 --> 00:47:24.620
There's actually a movement
within the psychology community

00:47:24.620 --> 00:47:28.720
called positive psychology
that is all about finding ways

00:47:28.720 --> 00:47:32.400
to increase the prosocial
behaviors is a term that they

00:47:32.400 --> 00:47:37.450
use, between people, and looking
at ways to influence and then

00:47:37.450 --> 00:47:41.440
measure if people are becoming
more empathic and more

00:47:41.440 --> 00:47:43.030
kind to each other.

00:47:43.030 --> 00:47:45.200
And so we actually had a
psychology graduate student

00:47:45.200 --> 00:47:49.950
at Berkeley develop a survey
to figure out in real terms

00:47:49.950 --> 00:47:53.160
whether the experiences of
watching this footage actually

00:47:53.160 --> 00:47:55.630
draws you out of yourself
and makes you someone who's

00:47:55.630 --> 00:47:57.180
thinking more about others.

